_Questions on this sheet probe details of ARM Cortex-M0 assembly language,
and also of its encoding as binary machine code. It can't be emphasised
enough that, though a lot of this detail is needed for the experience of understanding how a particular computer works (which every Computer Science
student should enjoy at some stage), it isn't detail that is worth memorising in
the medium term. I.e., you need to understand and be able to reproduce the process and the logic, but you don't need to memorise the details._

